<article class="article-body">

<p>A virtual chief of staff can run your company's operating rhythm from anywhere. But only if you hire for the right things. Title inflation is rampant, so test for evidence, not adjectives.</p>

<h2>Test for artifacts, not claims</h2>
<p>A real chief of staff leaves paper. Ask to see redacted versions of: a decision log, an initiative tracker, a leadership-meeting agenda template, and a board-pack structure they've run. No artifacts means no operating system, just an expensive meeting attendee.</p>

<h2>The three skills that matter</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Cadence</strong>: can they run a leadership rhythm where decisions get captured and chased?</li>
  <li><strong>Ambiguity</strong>: give a real, messy problem and 48 hours; score the structure of their plan and what they chose <em>not</em> to do.</li>
  <li><strong>Authority without power</strong>: they'll drive outcomes through people who don't report to them. Ask for a story where they did exactly that.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Red flags</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Talks strategy but can't show how they track execution.</li>
  <li>Wants to be in every meeting (presence ≠ output).</li>
  <li>No documentation habit: fatal for a remote role.</li>
  <li>Junior background pitched as senior: borrowed authority needs real operating experience.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How remote CoS engagements are structured</h2>
<p>Most start fractional: 10–25 hours a week anchored on the leadership cadence plus one or two strategic initiatives, on monthly terms. Time-zone overlap matters: a Nairobi-based CoS (EAT, UTC+3) covers European hours fully and US East mornings. (See <a href="/virtual-chief-of-staff/">virtual chief of staff</a> and <a href="/fractional-chief-of-staff/">fractional chief of staff</a>.)</p>

<h2>Before you start the search</h2>
<p>Make sure it's actually a CoS you need: <a href="/blog/when-to-hire-a-chief-of-staff/">five signs you're ready</a>, and the <a href="/blog/chief-of-staff-vs-executive-assistant/">CoS vs EA distinction</a>. If you'd rather start this week than run a 90-day search, <a href="/booking/">book a free call</a>.</p>

